span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/6/00 11:37:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Things to kill from levels 1-10</span><hr size=1> I'd like this to be a permanent thread, so post your level 1-10 spots here.   <BR>  <BR> I personally like Butcherblock and Misty Thicket.  Both of these zones have guards all over, and very few if any &quot;Insta-death&quot; mobs.  Very laid back 8). <BR>  <BR>  <BR> Rebo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujalia.showPublicProfile>Jalia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 3:57:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.sprynet.com/~nausicaa/minifigures/aqua.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Things to kill from levels 1-10</span><hr size=1>  <BR> This is a tough call because you're almost stuck with your own newbie zone for the first few levels no matter what, unless you know Norrath well or have friends to port you around. <BR>  <BR> On Faydwer, Greater Faydark is actually a good newbie zone except for all the people who regularly flood it... if you're on a low-population server (such as the PVP/racewar servers) then it can be a good place to level.  Butcherblock is also very nice, but I always got major lag there, don't know why, it was much worse with 30 people there than Greater Faydark with 100 people in it.  Clearly, though, a gnome mage should leave Steamfont as soon as possible... it's not a great zone to hunt in. <BR>  <BR> Around Freeport, Eastern Commons is nearly as bad as Greater Faydark... nice zone to hunt in, but usually filled with idiots.  North Ro is a good alternative.  I like the areas around Freeport, good places to hunt for well past 10th level. <BR>  <BR> Misty Thicket deserves it's reputation as one of the best places in the game to level, and it's well worth the trip to Rivervale when you can make it.  You can hunt to 11th level or higher there, all the way to 14th if you <em>really</em> want to, although gaining exp will become progressively more difficult after 11th.  But some people like the comfort of a zone with practically no insta-death mobs. <BR>  <BR> On the far side of the world, Qeynos/Qeynos Hills are okay hunting grounds but the hilly part of Qeynos is buggy, mobs teleport constantly.  Tox forest is without a doubt the worst newbie zone in the game, dark and empty and extremely buggy as well.  Everfrost, on the other hand, is IMO a better hunting area from 1-6 than Misty Thicket even; I've taken my Erudite and Human druid characters there to level (assuming you can make it through Blackburrow and avoid the vengeful skellies in Everfrost).  I really like Everfrost from 1 to 6.  After that it's very difficult to find mobs that you can gain exp from and still solo... Qeynos Hills is better to solo, but if you group up you can hunt the Everfrost plains or go to Blackburrow or Western Karana.  Usually, though, I find a way to get to Misty Thicket or Freeport, where the hunting from 6th to 10th level is much better, solo or grouped. <BR>  <BR>  <p><font size=-1 color=#ff0080>
<b>Aquaisha Blue</b></font><font size=-1 color=#8000ff>, cleric of 19th circle, tailor, <em>The Grove</em>, guild figurehead, On A Server Somewhere
