ould possibly head to the chessboard and kill pawns, slow spawn, but still good xp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Mingna</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 6:32:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   East Commonlands</span><hr size=1> Levels 6 to 9 have gone pretty quickly in East Commonlands, but only in groups. Young Kodiaks, giant spideys, blue scarabs and the fun of pitching in at one of the two orc camps and accidentally drawing a legonnaire and standing there with your gang and going toe to toe with it (because it resists almost all your spells !!) is a pulse pounding experience. Take alot of malachite, I never go without fifteen or so in my backpack and don't get too attached to that pet , 'casue something IS gonnas kill him. But the exp wracks up pretty fast. Not many guards. But a fair amount of close zones if discretion becomes the better part of valor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Damienn of Innoruuk</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 7:48:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Things to Kill from levels 1-10</span><hr size=1> I have a DE Mage in Nektulos and have soloed him exclusively to nearly level 9.  Lots of mobs from fire beetles all the way up to Shadowmen.  Only negative is you have to zone to sell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Zyvagorus</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 10:16:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   shadow men at what level??</span><hr size=1> Um... <BR>  <BR> You meant shadow wolves I hope. <BR>  <BR> Please do not attempt shadowed men until well into your twenties.  <BR>  <BR> Sorry to jump in there, but I had a vision of a level 8 magician reading that and stomping on down to the nearest shadowed man camp. <BR>  <BR> Good hunting all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Rythor</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 11:35:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   trains suck.......</span><hr size=1> im a human mage that started in Qeynos, and i think its great there. untill lvl4 i stayed in the newbie zones killing as many decaying skellies as i saw, their loot is incredible for low lvls i get 2pp per stack of bone chips.  anyway at lvl4 with my new pets in tow i went and camped the 3 gnolls that spawn just outside the entrace to BlackBurrow, that got me to lvl6 in two days of playing about 2 hours a day, plus it got me two stacks of gnoll fangs for the quest and a full suit of cloth armor.  then i spent half my time at the skellie ruins killing skellies and putrids but i always made sure to have a higher lvl watching for Pyzjn that could kill the dreads when they came. oh yeah i found the gray wolf spawning place witch spawns one every 20 or 30 seconds, and Holly Bitchstalker and Cros dont come there :).  anyway i spent the other half of my time in bb that gave the best xp and loot, but i got killed probably 10 or 20 times by trains between lvls 6 and 10.  trains suck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usunwolf.showPublicProfile>Sunwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/26/00 6:39:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/oelph/wolfy.jpg http://members.aol.com/oelph/wolfy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Steamfont is Good</span><hr size=1> I like Steamfont - never used too until starting my Mage (he's still only <img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)">.<br>
<br>
Obviously during levels 1-4 all the decaying skeletons, rats, kobold runts and so forth are your choice. Then at 5 and 6 try to get Kobold camp one. I soloed that camp through these entire two levels - including pulling the solo kobold on the hill side. Your level 4 AE spell is great here.<br>
<br>
At 7 things get slightly awkward - I think 7's probably the first hell level <img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)">. The area to your left after zoning into Steamfont from Lesser Fay is now home. Stay away from the skel's and puma's - these are nasty. Choice here is Kobold scouts and regular kobolds and rogue clockwork spiders (I love the sound these make when you hit them!).<br>
<br>
The camp nestled down the back of this little corner is good too - I actually had to 'break' the camp 3 times during level 7. Usually 3 out of the 5 con blue, the other two green so you can pull 3 kobolds to the hill side. The trick is to leave your pet guarding (/pet guard here) on the hill side, run down to the camp, burn and run back. Then act as the main tank getting of those AE's when you're able.<br>
<br>
I'm now at 8 so I'll be picking on all those skeleton's and odd puma that I saw roaming the hills there. I'm also going to move to the cogs down past the Mino Caves.<br>
<br>
Theoretically you could stay here till 14 killing harpies, drakes and the like with the occasional group killing mino's. I expect you'd be pretty fed up by then though. Time to move on.<br>
<br>
Happy travels!<br>
(Bubb, Gnomish Magi Extraordinaire - well in the making, despite what my username says. <img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)">). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udanur.showPublicProfile>Danur</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(3/14/00 5:47:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Steamfont is Good</span><hr size=1> Goto Qeynos and kill rabid wolves the quest is awesome.  I make a lvl off of 8 or 9 pelts.  Did this from 3 to 9 (lvl 3 took 4 pelts and about 2 pelts extra per lvl).  Great quest and when you kill wolves you get a spell that sells for 7 gp.  Loot is poor but the exp gets you through the lvls.  The quest finishes with the person casting cure disease on you so you can got get more. <p><center><img src=http://www.lamserv.com/temp/danur.jpg></center><BR><BR><BR>

Only ding ruinin da world is dem dam tree huggers and half breeds.  </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> tinkero</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(3/31/00 6:14:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   quick way from1-10 with some spare change</span><hr size=1> I a gnome magician had a very easy time getting from 1 to 10. from 1-4 just hunt diseased rats,decaying skels, and rats. hunt kobolds at the the camp till lvl 6 or 7. Ocassionally u can get permission to loot guards that high lvls r killing(very good money). At lvl 6 or 7 head over to crushbone and kill easy centurions near the entrance to crushbone. They drop belts which can be sold for 1pp each if u find the right buyer. Take all of the money u got from belts and buy a lotta lego pads. they sell for 2pp. Now, head over to kaladim and go into the warrior guild. I forgot his name but i think the guy who gives the quest is on the right side of the hall. Give him 2 belts at a time. This will result in very awesome,quick experience and some pp left over from guard looting. good luck all fellow mages!<br>
<br>
P.S. almost forgot,use fire pet from lvl 4-8, then water all the way after that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Frobozz</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(6/16/00 5:49:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Be prepared for a shock...</span><hr size=1> In the unlikely event you start an Erudite Magician, there IS a way to level your character without going to Qeynos.  It saves you quite a bit of money since you don't have to get a bind and you get better prices at Erudin for stuff you kill.<br>
<br>
Note: Consider making your mage AGNOSTIC.<br>
<br>
Level 1-2: Possibly the easiest level to get if you are careful.  Just hang around near the Erudin porch and kill every moss snake you find.  There is a hut west of the porch with a hill where little critters crawl by...plus there's good light from the hut.  Straight south from the porch is good too, be sure to use your candle.<br>
<br>
Level 3-4: Run to Paineel!  Yes, you can hunt there and the skeleton guards watching the newbie area there will NOT hurt you.  The problem is, they also won't help you if you get in trouble.  Kill everything in sight!  If you are getting clobbered by that fire beetle gang, undead rat, or Noclin's pet, run quickly to the zone!  It's not that far.<br>
<br>
By now, you should have killed enough decayed skeletons for weapons (decent loot) to sell.  You should be able to afford your Lev 4 pet and Gate.  If you have money left over, a lantern is a great idea (unless you have are using a 2h blunt weapon).<br>
<br>
Level 5-6: Best bet for exp are Kobold scouts and watchers on the Paineel side.  There is also a 3 kobold camp on the Paineel side of Toxx which occasionally spawns a shaman.  They can still be solo'd.  The 4 kobold camp near the bridge should probably be grouped since skeletons walk by a lot...especially when you are OOM.<br>
<br>
